[{"i": 361, "t": "Every quarter"}, {"i": 362, "t": "&gt;"}, {"i": 363, "t": "Kritik:"}, {"i": 364, "t": "valproat"}, {"i": 365, "t": "postpartum-aged women"}, {"i": 366, "t": "Due to neural tube defect and cause of cognitive impairment"}, {"i": 367, "t": "only with effective contraception"}, {"i": 368, "t": ", after other options have been evaluated first."}, {"i": 369, "t": "Karbamazepin:"}, {"i": 370, "t": "CBC, liver – baseline, 1 month, quarterly;"}, {"i": 371, "t": "HLA-B*1502 test"}, {"i": 372, "t": "In patients of Asian origin (Stevens-Johnson risk);"}, {"i": 373, "t": "Level drop due to auto-induction in the first 4 weeks – check level."}, {"i": 374, "t": "Lamotrigin:"}, {"i": 375, "t": "Slow titration"}, {"i": 376, "t": "– Stevens-Johnson syndrome risk;"}, {"i": 377, "t": "Starting 25 mg per week"}, {"i": 378, "t": ", to target dose within 4–8 weeks;"}, {"i": 379, "t": "Along with valproate:"}, {"i": 380, "t": "starting dose 12.5 mg"}, {"i": 381, "t": "– valproate slows lamotrigin metabolism;"}, {"i": 382, "t": "If a skin reaction occurs –"}, {"i": 383, "t": "immediately discontinue."}, {"i": 384, "t": "A.4. Monitoring of SSRIs and SNRIs"}, {"i": 385, "t": "Hiponatremiya riski"}, {"i": 386, "t": "– especially in elderly, in those using diuretics;"}, {"i": 387, "t": "Bazal Na"}, {"i": 388, "t": ", after 1 month, then with symptom;"}, {"i": 389, "t": "Increased suicidality"}, {"i": 390, "t": "especially with onset under 25 years — close monitoring during first 1-2 months;"}, {"i": 391, "t": "QTc uzanma"}, {"i": 392, "t": "– escitalopram, citalopram (at high doses);"}, {"i": 393, "t": "Serotonin sindromu"}, {"i": 394, "t": "(MAOI or triptan, etc., in combination) – symptom education."}, {"i": 395, "t": "A.5. Benzodiazepine use"}, {"i": 396, "t": "Maximum duration: 2–4 weeks"}, {"i": 397, "t": "Long-term use inevitably leads to addiction;"}, {"i": 398, "t": "Azaltma sxemi (tapering):"}, {"i": 399, "t": "25% every 2 weeks, sometimes slower;"}, {"i": 400, "t": "Re-experiencing symptoms."}, {"i": 401, "t": "(rebound anxiety, insomnia, tremor) is normal and temporary."}, {"i": 402, "t": "A.6. Psixoterapiya monitorinqi"}, {"i": 403, "t": "Quality indicators:"}, {"i": 404, "t": "Session duration, frequency;"}, {"i": 405, "t": "Patient symptom scales (PHQ-9, GAD-7, etc.)"}, {"i": 406, "t": "every 4–6 weeks"}, {"i": 407, "t": "Functional indicators;"}, {"i": 408, "t": "Assessment of therapeutic alliance (Working Alliance Inventory)."}, {"i": 409, "t": "Achieving external goals;"}, {"i": 410, "t": "Signs of relapse."}, {"i": 411, "t": "Supervision and collegial consultation – for complex patients and desiring clinicians."}, {"i": 412, "t": "APPENDIX C"}, {"i": 413, "t": "PSYCHIATRIC EMERGENCY SITUATIONS"}, {"i": 414, "t": "This appendix provides a practical approach to psychiatric conditions that are life-threatening or require acute clinical evaluation."}, {"i": 415, "t": "C.1. Aktiv intihar riski"}, {"i": 416, "t": "Primary assessment:"}, {"i": 417, "t": "Are there suicidal thoughts? Plans? Means?"}, {"i": 418, "t": "Proximity, specificity:"}, {"i": 419, "t": "\"Today evening in the yard with a...\" vs general \"Sometimes I want to die\";"}, {"i": 420, "t": "Previous attempts"}, {"i": 421, "t": "– the strongest predictor;"}, {"i": 422, "t": "Substance intoxication"}, {"i": 423, "t": "– inhibition decreased;"}, {"i": 424, "t": "Protektiv faktorlar"}, {"i": 425, "t": "– family, religious beliefs, future plans."}, {"i": 426, "t": "High risk signs:"}, {"i": 427, "t": "Concrete plan + access to means;"}, {"i": 428, "t": "Recent situational change (loss, severe illness);"}, {"i": 429, "t": "Loneliness + stubbornness;"}, {"i": 430, "t": "Psychosis or severe depression;"}, {"i": 431, "t": "New onset or profound hypomania (energy returns + mood remains low);"}, {"i": 432, "t": "Adult male + disability + alcohol."}, {"i": 433, "t": "Management:"}, {"i": 434, "t": "Low-moderate risk:"}, {"i": 435, "t": "Safety plan"}, {"i": 436, "t": "– written;"}, {"i": 437, "t": "Reducing access to means (gun removal, medication in small quantities)"}, {"i": 438, "t": "Close ambulatory monitoring (re-evaluate within 24-48 hours);"}, {"i": 439, "t": "Crisis hotline number;"}, {"i": 440, "t": "Family involvement (with consent)."}, {"i": 441, "t": "High risk:"}, {"i": 442, "t": "hospitalization"}, {"i": 443, "t": "(voluntary or involuntary);"}, {"i": 444, "t": "Close supervision – 1:1 if very high;"}, {"i": 445, "t": "Restriction of suicide methods (sharp objects, rope, window);"}, {"i": 446, "t": "Controlled medication intake."}, {"i": 447, "t": "Involuntary hospitalization within the Azerbaijani framework:"}, {"i": 448, "t": "\"On psychiatric assistance\" Law of the Republic of Azerbaijan;"}, {"i": 449, "t": "For involuntary hospitalization"}, {"i": 450, "t": "decision by two psychiatrists"}, {"i": 451, "t": "and legal procedure;"}, {"i": 452, "t": "72-hour emergency observation followed by a court order."}, {"i": 453, "t": "C.2. Delirium tremens and alcohol withdrawal"}, {"i": 454, "t": "Simptomlar:"}, {"i": 455, "t": "tremor"}, {"i": 456, "t": "– hands, then general;"}, {"i": 457, "t": "Anxiety, agitation;"}, {"i": 458, "t": "hallucination"}, {"i": 459, "t": "– visual, tactile (\"bugs crawling on me\");"}, {"i": 460, "t": "Disorientation;"}, {"i": 461, "t": "Autonom hiperaktivlik"}, {"i": 462, "t": "– tachycardia, pressure, sweating, heating;"}, {"i": 463, "t": "Tutmalar"}, {"i": 464, "t": "Treatment (in ICU or IMU setting):"}, {"i": 465, "t": "benzodiazepine"}, {"i": 466, "t": "diazepam 10–20 mg IV/IM every 15–20 min"}, {"i": 467, "t": "until sedation is achieved; then maintenance regimen;"}, {"i": 468, "t": "Alternative: lorazepam (in those with hepatic dysfunction);"}, {"i": 469, "t": "Tiamin 100-300 mq IV"}, {"i": 470, "t": "– Prevention of Wernicke's encephalopathy."}, {"i": 471, "t": "Before glucose administration"}, {"i": 472, "t": "Fluids and electrolytes"}, {"i": 473, "t": "Recovery;"}, {"i": 474, "t": "Magnesium sulfate, potassium – often low;"}, {"i": 475, "t": "Mortality: untreated 15-20%, with adequate treatment <1%."}, {"i": 476, "t": "CIWA-Ar scale — for monitoring."}, {"i": 477, "t": "C.3. Serotonin sindromu"}, {"i": 478, "t": "Cause"}, {"i": 479, "t": "SSRI + MAOI, SSRI + triptan, SSRI + tramadol, SSRI + linezolid, SSRI + methylene blue, etc."}, {"i": 480, "t": "Simptomlar:"}, {"i": 481, "t": "Mental change"}, {"i": 482, "t": "– agitation, confusion;"}, {"i": 483, "t": "Autonom"}, {"i": 484, "t": "– tachycardia, hypertension, hyperthermia, sweating;"}, {"i": 485, "t": "Neyromuskulyar"}, {"i": 486, "t": "– tremor, hiperrefleksiya,"}, {"i": 487, "t": "klonus"}, {"i": 488, "t": "(lower extremity – specific sign)."}, {"i": 489, "t": "Treatment:"}, {"i": 490, "t": "Immediate discontinuation of causative medication"}, {"i": 491, "t": "Support — fluids, electrolytes, cooling;"}, {"i": 492, "t": "In severe cases"}, {"i": 493, "t": "cyproheptadine 12 mg initial, 2 mg every hour maximum 32 mg/day"}, {"i": 494, "t": "Invasive intervention (intubation) in severe hyperthermia."}, {"i": 495, "t": "C.4. Antipsixotik Malign Sindrom (NMS)"}, {"i": 496, "t": "Cause"}, {"i": 497, "t": "Antipsychotics (especially high potency, haloperidol), acute initiation or dose increase."}, {"i": 498, "t": "Symptoms (4 main):"}, {"i": 499, "t": "Muscle stiffness"}, {"i": 500, "t": " (\"lead pipe\");"}, {"i": 501, "t": "Hipertermiya"}, {"i": 502, "t": "(38–42°C);"}, {"i": 503, "t": "Autonomic lability"}, {"i": 504, "t": "(high blood pressure, tachycardia, sweating);"}, {"i": 505, "t": "Mental state change"}, {"i": 506, "t": "(confusion → stupor → coma)."}, {"i": 507, "t": "Laboratoriya:"}, {"i": 508, "t": "CPK acutely elevated."}, {"i": 509, "t": " (>1000), myoglobinuria, leukocytosis, ALT/AST elevated."}, {"i": 510, "t": "Treatment (ICU):"}, {"i": 511, "t": "Immediate discontinuation of antipsychotics"}, {"i": 512, "t": "Cooling."}, {"i": 513, "t": "Fluids (risk of rhabdomyolysis and acute kidney failure);"}, {"i": 514, "t": "Dantrolen"}, {"i": 515, "t": "1-2.5 mg/kg IV – reduces muscle rigidity;"}, {"i": 516, "t": "Bromokriptin"}, {"i": 517, "t": "2.5-5 mg every 8 hours – dopamine agonist;"}, {"i": 518, "t": "ECT in non-responsive cases."}, {"i": 519, "t": "Deathfulness:"}, {"i": 520, "t": "5-20% with adequate treatment."}, {"i": 521, "t": "C.5. Acute dystonia"}, {"i": 522, "t": "Cause"}, {"i": 523, "t": "Antipsychotic initiation, especially potent D2 antagonists."}, {"i": 524, "t": "Simptomlar:"}, {"i": 525, "t": "Acute muscle spasms – neck (torticollis), tongue, eyes (oculogyric crisis), certain esophageal spasm;"}, {"i": 526, "t": "Life-threatening – laryngeal spasm."}, {"i": 527, "t": "Treatment:"}, {"i": 528, "t": "Difenhidramin"}, {"i": 529, "t": "50 mg IM/IV – relief within 15 minutes;"}, {"i": 530, "t": "Benztropin"}, {"i": 531, "t": "1-2 mg IM/IV;"}, {"i": 532, "t": "Reducing or changing the dose of antipsychotics"}, {"i": 533, "t": "Prophylactic anticholinergic in high-risk patients."}, {"i": 534, "t": "C.6. Acute mania and psychomotor agitation"}, {"i": 535, "t": "Management:"}, {"i": 536, "t": " - Oral preferred: haloperidol 2-5 mg + lorazepam 1-2 mg;"}, {"i": 537, "t": " - IM regimen: haloperidol 5 mg + lorazepam 2 mg (50/50 syringe) or olanzapine IM 10 mg;"}, {"i": 538, "t": "Safe environment"}, {"i": 539, "t": "– quiet, free from stimuli;"}, {"i": 540, "t": "Verbal de-eskalasiya"}, {"i": 541, "t": "first step;"}, {"i": 542, "t": "Medication:"}, {"i": 543, "t": "involuntary hospitalization"}, {"i": 544, "t": "By instruction;"}, {"i": 545, "t": "Physical restraint"}, {"i": 546, "t": "– only as a last resort, personal life threat, short-term."}, {"i": 547, "t": "C.7. Acute psychosis"}, {"i": 548, "t": "Similar protocol as above. Differential: organic causes, substance intoxication, postpartum psychosis, NMS."}, {"i": 549, "t": "C.8. Katatoniya"}, {"i": 550, "t": "Simptomlar:"}, {"i": 551, "t": "Stupor, mutism;"}, {"i": 552, "t": "Catalepsy ('waxy flexibility');"}, {"i": 553, "t": "Negativism;"}, {"i": 554, "t": "Mannerisms, stereotypies;"}, {"i": 555, "t": "Eholalia, ekopraksiya."}, {"i": 556, "t": "First-line treatment:"}, {"i": 557, "t": "Lorazepam 1-2 mq IV/IM test"}, {"i": 558, "t": "– Significant response within 1-2 hours → diagnosis and treatment of catatonia;"}, {"i": 559, "t": "If response is obtained — increase to a dose of 4–24 mg/day;"}, {"i": 560, "t": "No answer –"}, {"i": 561, "t": "ECT"}, {"i": 562, "t": "Second-line, highly effective;"}, {"i": 563, "t": "Avoiding antipsychotics"}, {"i": 564, "t": "During acute phase – NMS administration may be provocative."}, {"i": 565, "t": "Search for cause"}, {"i": 566, "t": "organic (encephalitis, epilepsy), mood disorders, schizophrenia, autism, certain substances."}, {"i": 567, "t": "APPENDIX D"}, {"i": 568, "t": "MILITARY-MEDICAL EXPERTISE (IN AZERBAIJAN)"}, {"i": 569, "t": "This appendix provides practical guidance on psychiatric aspects for assessing fitness for military service in the Republic of Azerbaijan."}, {"i": 570, "t": "D.1. Legal basis"}, {"i": 571, "t": "\"On military service call-up\""}, {"i": 572, "t": "Law of the Republic of Azerbaijan;"}, {"i": 573, "t": "Regulation on military-medical expertise;"}, {"i": 574, "t": "Ministry of Defense"}, {"i": 575, "t": "Normative acts;"}, {"i": 576, "t": "Table of diseases"}, {"i": 577, "t": "– divided into halves: mild/severe degrees, groups A–D."}, {"i": 578, "t": "D.2. Psychiatric assessment structure"}, {"i": 579, "t": "Main expert examination:"}, {"i": 580, "t": "Complaints and history (patient and close relatives);"}, {"i": 581, "t": "Previous medical records;"}, {"i": 582, "t": "Clinical interview and mental status examination;"}, {"i": 583, "t": "Experimental-Psychological Examination"}, {"i": 584, "t": "(EPM) – by psychologist;"}, {"i": 585, "t": "Laboratory and instrumental examinations when necessary;"}]